<br>
<br>
A previous topic here suggested purchasing grapes or some such food for monks because of its weight of 0.1 lbs.<br>
<br>
OK-- Someone tell me if I'm smoking crack, need to go back to elementary school and relearn basic math, but...<br>
<br>
I'm the kind of person that will fill a 10 slot with 100 rations and 100 milk so there is no need to return to the store for many days, and any group member will have some food if they run out.  I don't recal the exact weight of rations or milk, but I was sure it was above 0.1 lbs.  Some food IS 0.1 lbs. though, so lets use that as our example.  <br>
If I am carrying 100 food weighted at 0.1 lbs, and 100 drink at 0.1 lbs as well, what is my calculated weight? 100 * 0.1 SHOULD come out to be 10 lbs.  SO, in that bag I shouldbe carrying 20 extra lbs ---- But I don't.  At the very best I will be carrying 4 lbs.  Test it out some time when purchasing food.  I'm sure you've all seen this occurence.  I guess in a game of surreality (to some, in any case, LOL), I'd love to see us lugging around 20 lbs of food rather than some pro-rated 4 lbs.  Almost makes it pointless to then carry the food in a weight reduction bag, because its being reduced all by its own.  Perhaps 'pack mites' are eating it.....<br>
<br>
But then......who wants to see us reduced from carrying an obscene amount of 10'slots (8?) fully loaded with bronze armor from loots, or FS's, when in reality we shouldn't be able to. =-)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
